[KEEP] The Pandora Papers are 11.9 million leaked documents that were announced by the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists (ICIJ) on October 2, 2021 to be published beginning on October 3, 2021. [KEEP] The organisations described the document leak as their most expansive exposé of financial secrecy yet. [KEEP] In the Pandora Papers, the ICIJ worked on 11.9 million documents, making this the largest offshore data leak in history, surpassing the Panama Papers, which were a leak of 11.5 million confidential documents. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cOver 100 billionaires, 30 current and former leaders, and 300 public officials were named in the first leaks on October 3, 2021. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cThough not illegal, Tony Blair was shown in the papers to have saved £312,000 in Stamp Duty on the purchase of a £6.45million property in London by purchasing Romanstone International Limited, a British Virgin Islands company. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\c
[KEEP] The Pandora Papers are 11.9 million leaked documents (comprising 2.9 terabytes of data) that were published by the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists (ICIJ) beginning on 3 October 2021. [KEEP] The news organisations of the ICIJ described the document leak as their most expansive exposé of financial secrecy yet, containing documents, images, emails and spreadsheets from 14 financial service companies, in nations including Panama, Switzerland and the UAE, surpassing their previous release of the Panama Papers in 2016, which had 11.5 million confidential documents. [KEEP] At the time of the release of the papers, the ICIJ said it is not identifying its source for the documents. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cUp to an estimated US$32 trillion (excluding non-monetary valuables such as real estate, art, and jewelry) may be hidden from being taxed, according to news reports. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cIn total, 35 current and former national leaders appear in the leak, alongside 400 officials from nearly 100 countries. [KEEP] Among those names are former British Prime Minister Tony Blair, Chilean President Sebastián Piñera, Kenyan President Uhuru Kenyatta, Montenegrin President Milo Đukanović, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, Qatari Emir Sheikh Tamim, Gabonese President Ali Bongo Ondimba and Ecuadorian President Guillermo Lasso. [KEEP] More than 100 billionaires, 29,000 offshore accounts, 30 current and former leaders, and 336 politicians were named in the first leaks on 3 October 2021. [KEEP] <Disclosures> \c\cKing Abdullah II of Jordan is one of the main figures named in the papers, with documents showing he had invested over US$100 million in property across the UK and the US; they included houses in Cliffside Drive, Malibu, Washington, D.C., London and Ascot in the UK. [KEEP] A UK company controlled by Cherie Blair was shown to have acquired a £6.45 million property in London by purchasing Romanstone International Limited, a British Virgin Islands company; had the property been acquired directly, £312,000 would have been payable in stamp duty. [KEEP] Tony Blair's name appears in a statement of joint income for the associated mortgage. [KEEP] The papers also reveal how an office block owned by the Aliyev family was sold to the Crown Estate, the sovereign's public estate, for £66 million in 2018, netting the Aliyevs a £31 million profit. [KEEP] Another office block worth £33 million was sold to the family in 2009, and was gifted to Heyder Aliyev, son of Azerbaijan's President Aliyev. [KEEP] Kenyan President Uhuru Kenyatta was also mentioned, despite being quoted in 2018 as stating, "Every public servant's assets must be declared publicly so that people can question and ask – what is legitimate?" [KEEP] Kenyatta and six members of his family have been linked to 13 offshore companies. [KEEP] <Disclosures> \c\cOther global names mentioned include Shakira, who was incorporating new offshore entities while going on trial for tax evasion; model Claudia Schiffer; Indian cricket player Sachin Tendulkar; Alexandre Cazes, the founder of the dark web site AlphaBay, used to deal in illegal drugs; Pakistan's finance minister, Shaukat Fayaz Ahmed Tarin, and several of family members of Pakistan's top generals; and the CEO of Channel One Russia, Konstantin Ernst. [KEEP] Miguel Bosé, Pep Guardiola and Julio Iglesias are also named. [KEEP] <Disclosures> \c\cThe leaked files come from 14 offshore service providers that help clients establish companies in secrecy jurisdictions. [KEEP] <Data sources> \c\c [KEEP] An ICIJ report focused on the Panamanian law firm of Alemán, Cordero, Galindo & Lee, or Alcogal, saying it was the "law firm of the Latin American elite" that created at least 14,000 shell companies and trusts in tax havens. [KEEP] Alcogal was mentioned more than any other offshore provider in the leaked documents. [KEEP] <Data sources> \c\c [KEEP] The ICIJ worked with journalists in 117 countries including news organizations such as The Washington Post, L\'Espresso, Le Monde, El País, Süddeutsche Zeitung, PBS program Frontline, the Australian Broadcasting Corporation, The Guardian, and the BBC’s Panorama. [KEEP] <Data sources - Alcogal law firm> \c\cIn Pakistan, Prime Minister Imran Khan said that all citizens mentioned in the Pandora Papers would be investigated and appropriate action taken in case of wrongdoing. [KEEP] <Newsrooms> \c\c
[KEEP] On October 4, 2021, Facebook and their subsidiaries including Instagram and WhatsApp were made globally unavailable. [KEEP] The outage is ongoing and the cause is not yet known. [RM] Other popular social media platforms, such as Twitter were struggling to maintain the load of users coming to their platforms following the outage. [ADD] Security experts identified the problem as possibly being DNS-related and was most particularly related to BGP.
[KEEP] The deadly moment magnitude 5.9 Mw  quake struck near the anniversary of the 2005 Kashmir earthquake which killed 87,000 people. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cPakistan is directly influenced by the ongoing oblique convergence between the Indian Plate and Eurasian Plate. [KEEP] Along the northern margin of the India-Eurasia convergent boundary is the Main Himalayan Thrust which accommodates north-south continental collision. [KEEP] Thrust faulting in the Hindu Kush and Himalaya region is the direct result of the plate interaction. [KEEP] In the Balochistan region, the convergence is highly oblique, involving the large Chaman Fault; a strike-slip structure and many thrust faults. [KEEP] The 2005 Kashmir earthquake occurred near the vicinity of the Main Himalayan Thrust. [KEEP] The more recent and larger manitude 7.7 quake in 2013 in Balochistan was the result of oblique-slip faulting along this highly oblique boundary. [KEEP] That earthquake killed at least 800 and caused major damage in the province. [KEEP] <Tectonic setting> \c\cAccording to the U.S. Geological Survey, the earthquake occurred during the rupture of a thrust fault under the Sulaiman Mountains and Central Brāhui Range. [KEEP] It was followed by a magnitude 4.6 aftershock. [KEEP] It was the largest earthquake in Pakistan since the a major tremor in 2013 which occurred nearby. [ADD] The earthquake was revised from an initial estimation of 5.7 at 20.8 km depth to 5.9 at 9.0 km. [KEEP] At least 20 people died, mostly women and children. [KEEP] An unspecified number of residents were buried under the rubble of collapsed buildings, and rescued by survivors. [KEEP] The number of injured people stands at 300, with many hospitals in Balochistan overwhelmed by the influx of patients. [KEEP] According to the Provincial Disaster Management Authority (Khyber Pakhtunkhwa) (PDMA), severe damage was reported in the Harnai District and Shahrag area, where at least 70 homes were affected. [KEEP] Damage was also reported in the cities of Sibi and Quetta. [KEEP] <Impact> \c\cFollowing the quake, troops from the Pakistan Army were dispatched in Harnai to aid in recsue and relief operations. [KEEP] At least nine injured victims in need of medical treatment were transported via helicopters from the affected region to Quetta. [KEEP] The Inter-Services Public Relations, army, medical personnel, response workers, and officials are working together to coordinate the rescue and relief works. [KEEP] A team of search and rescue individuals from Rawalpindi was sent to Harnai to find survivors among the wreckage. [KEEP] "} <Response> \c\c
