EEP] <Investigation> \c\c
[KEEP] On November 5, 2021 an oil tanker collided with a truck in Freetown, Sierra Leone. [KEEP] The collision resulted in an explosion that killed at least 99 and injured around 100. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cFreetown is a port city with a population of over 1 million people. [KEEP] It has faced several disasters in the past. [KEEP] In March, a major fire in one of the city's slums left 80 injured and more than 5000 displaced. [KEEP] In 2017, heavy rains triggered mudslides that killed over 1000 people. [KEEP] <Background> \c\cThe collision and subsequent explosion is believed to have happened at 22:00 GMT on November 5 in the Wellington suburb at a junction outside Choithram Supermarket. [KEEP] Fuel spilled before igniting and mayor Yvonne Aki Sawyerr stated on Facebook that people flocked to collect the fuel from the leaking vehicle. [KEEP] <Event> \c\cReports state that a bus full of people were "completely" burnt and nearby shops and markets caught on fire after fuel spilled over the streets. [RM] <Event> [ADD] <Event> \c\cAt least 99 people were confirmed dead in the tragedy, and more than 100 injured. \c\c [RM] The mortuary at Connaught Hospital has received 92 bodies so far. [KEEP] He added that rescue efforts at the scene had ended. [KEEP] Several people are in critical condition. [KEEP] According to a staff member of Connaught Hospital's intensive care unit, about 30 severally burned victims are not expected to survive. [KEEP] President Julius Maada Bio, who was attending the United Nations climate talks, offered condolences and promised support to the victims\' families. [KEEP] Vice President Mohamed Juldeh Jalloh visited two hospitals. [KEEP] Journalist Omar Fofana reported that the hospital services have been stretched. [KEEP] <Aftermath> \c\c
[KEEP] On November 5, 2021, a human crush occurred during the first night of the Astroworld Festival, a music event operated by rapper Travis Scott. [KEEP] Eight people died during the event with the cause of death still under investigation. [KEEP] A further twenty-three were hospitalized and more than 300 people were treated for injuries at the festival's field hospital. [KEEP] <Summary> \c\cAstroworld Festival is an annual music festival run by American rapper Travis Scott, held in Houston, Texas. [KEEP] In 2019, three people were injured in a stampede at the Astroworld Festival. [KEEP] <Background> \c\cIn 2021, the festival had approximately 50,000 attendees. [KEEP] The Houston Fire Department had fifty-five in-service units present at the festival, including 367 police officers and 241 security officers. [KEEP] Earlier on November 5, hundreds of fans surged at the festival's perimeter in an attempt to get in, knocking over metal detectors. [KEEP] Scott's performance was live streamed on Apple Music. [KEEP] <Background> \c\cOn the first night of the Astroworld Festival, the appearance of Scott on the stage led people to push towards the stage en masse, leading to a crush. [KEEP] According to Houston Fire Chief Sam Peña, between 9:00 p.m. and 9:15 p.m., the crowd began "to compress toward the front of the stage". [KEEP] As people began to fall and get injured, additional panic ensued. [KEEP] Peña stated the most fatal events occurred after 9:30 p.m. [KEEP] The show's paramedics were seen performing CPR on unconscious attendees. [RM] At approximately 9:38 p.m., 17 people were transferred to hospitals. <Crush> \c\cScott, along with stage crew, paused during his 75-minute performance when he noticed attendees in distress near the stage. [ADD] At 9:38 p.m., officials declared a "mass causality event" and 17 people were transferred to hospitals. [ADD] Peña stated that medical personnel was "quickly overwhelmed" as the amount of injuries surged. [KEEP] Two members of Scott's staff approached him on stage, though he shooed them away and resumed his performance. [KEEP] A concertgoer was filmed informing a cameraman that "people are dying", but another audience member told him that the crowd would take care of it. [KEEP] <Crush> \c\cAt least eight people died, ranging from the ages of 16 to 23. [KEEP] The cause of death is still under investigation. [KEEP] <Victims> \c\cTwenty-three others were evacuated to local hospitals, including eleven people found in a state of cardiac arrest. [KEEP] Drug overdose is being investigated as a potential cause of cardiac arrest. [KEEP] In all, more than 300 people were treated for injuries in a field hospital at the festival itself. [KEEP] <Victims> \c\cAs a result, the second night on November 6 was cancelled. [KEEP] A reunification center was set up for families searching for relatives. [KEEP] On November 6, Texas governor Greg Abbott stated: "What happened at Astroworld Festival last night was tragic, and our hearts are with those who lost their lives and those who were injured in the terrifying crowd surge." [KEEP] <Aftermath> \c\cScott stated he would support the incident's investigation and that he wants to help heal the Houston community. [KEEP] Kylie Jenner, Scott's girlfriend, was criticized for Instagram posts depicting the crowd, including one with an ambulance attempting to make its way through the crowd. [KEEP] Jenner and her sister, Kendall Jenner, were not injured during the event. [KEEP] <Aftermath> \c\c
